Release Notes:

As one-half of Duoteque, Paulo Lodde made his mark on the
clubbing community with his sharp electro-techno dancefloor
anthems, but his sole focus is now his solo work as Dusty Kid.
After releasing his "I Love Richie" record as an ode to Mr
Hawtin, the M_nus man himself started to play Dusty Kid's
maximalist take on modern techno, which has won Lodde many
fans around the globe.

A Raver's Diary is Lodde's first attempt at a full album, and
merges his more direct dance floor tracks with the deeper,
more hypnotic side of his productions. Apart from the
previously released "Cowboys" (which has been reworked for the
record), all of the material featured has been produced
especially for the album, with Boxer promising a coherent and
immersive listening experience once the record drops in April.
